content.text:
Ah! So line 320 has `) : (` which means the "plan" ternary is: `step === "plan" ? <form>...</form> : <form>...</form>` - the second part is the payment step. So the structure should be:

```
step === "plan" ? (
  // plan form
) : step === "payment" ? (
  // payment form  
) : step === "card_payment" ? (
  // card payment
) : null
```

But we currently have:
```
step === "plan" ? (
  // plan form
) : (
  // payment form
) : step === "card_payment" ? (  // <-- This is wrong!
```

The issue is that after the payment form closes with `)`, we immediately have another ternary `: step === "card_payment" ?` which is invalid. We need to change the payment form to also be a conditional. Let me fix this:

